  "articleSummary": "The article argues that fixed-priority dropdowns (e.g., P1–P4) create a \"Priority Trap\" where teams endlessly invent higher labels (P0, P00) instead of acknowledging that priorities are fluid and context-dependent. It critiques this as \"engineering theater\" and recommends alternatives like unbounded numeric fields, multidimensional scoring (e.g., MoSCoW), or disciplined backlog pruning. The tone is humorous and critical, targeting developers and project managers who use Jira or similar tools. Recurring metaphors include the \"z-index war\" (priority inflation) and the \"Bizzaro Trophy Room\" (a backlog of never-shipped work).",
